name: NY Secretary of State Robert J. Rodriguez
tweet: To then hear that there is no specific language protecting tenants under Baez in the new Blueprint is unacceptable.  Under no ambiguous terms, language in legislation must protect tenants under Baez and @NYCHA must adhere to the federal court agreement for all its units.

name: NY Secretary of State Robert J. Rodriguez
tweet: .@NYCHA claims those 62,000 units under RAD are under private management and therefore no longer covered by the agreement.   Today, a federal judge will hold a hearing over the classification of these units under RAD in relation to Baez.

name: NY Secretary of State Robert J. Rodriguez
tweet: After @metroiafny filed suit, a federal judge oversaw the settlement agreement that mandated @NYCHA to abate mold and establish an independent Ombudsperson to facilitate the clean ups.   Since then, NYCHA has pulled 62,000 of its units out of the mold agreement as part of RAD.
